					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4280523#post-3634129</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4280523/tjalla#post-3634129</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 16 Nov 2017 20:21:47 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Shaggydredlocks</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1722371</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Eh, this falls short of upvote-worthy for me. I don't think there's enough conflict to really become invested in the character's choice - which boils down to be not much of one. This undermines everything that came before, making her feelings towards Hanna seem wholly inauthentic - which would be fine, if that was the point, but that isn't reflected on either.</p> <p>The whole thing feels shallow when it could easily not be, so it's a definite -1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
